((~b) & d), a, b, x, s, t);\n}\n\nfunction gg(a, b, c, d, x, s, t) {\nreturn cmn((b & d) | (c & (~d)), a, b, x, s, t);\n}\n\nfunction hh(a, b, c, d, x, s, t) {\nreturn cmn(b ^ c ^ d, a, b, x, s, correctTarifForCopy(inputString) {\r\n    if (typeof inputString !== 'string') {\r\n        return \"0.00\";\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    let cleanedString = inputString.replace(/\\s/g, '');\r\n\r\n    const hasDot = cleanedString.includes('.');\r\n    const hasComma = cleanedString.includes(',');\r\n\r\n    let numberToParse;\r\n\r\n    if (hasDot && hasComma) {\r\n        const lastDotIndex = cleanedString.lastIndexOf('.');\r\n        const lastCommaIndex = cleanedString.lastIndexOf(',');\r\n\r\n        let isCommaDecimal = false;\r\n        let isDotDecimal = false;\r\n        if (lastCommaIndex !== -1 && (cleanedString.length - 1 - lastCommaIndex >= 1 && cleanedString.length - 1 - lastCommaIndex <= 3)) {\r\n            isCommaDecimal = true;\r\n        }\r\n        if (lastDotIndex !== -1 && (cleanedString.length - 1 - lastDotIndex >= 1 && cleanedString.length - 1 - lastDotIndex <= 3)) {\r\n            isDotDecimal = true;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        if (isCommaDecimal && !isDotDecimal) {\r\n            numberToParse = cleanedString.replace(/\\./g, '').replace(',', '.');\r\n        } else if (isDotDecimal && !isCommaDecimal) {\r\n            numberToParse = cleanedString.replace(/,/g, '');\r\n        } else if (isCommaDecimal && isDotDecimal) {\r\n            if (lastCommaIndex > lastDotIndex) {\r\n                numberToParse = cleanedString.replace(/\\./g, '').replace(',', '.');\r\n            } else {\r\n                numberToParse = cleanedString.replace(/,/g, '');\r\n            }\r\n        } else {\r\n            numberToParse = cleanedString.replace(/[,.]/g, '');\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    else if (hasComma) {\r\n        const lastCommaIndex = cleanedString.lastIndexOf(',');\r\n        if (lastCommaIndex !== -1 && (cleanedString.length - 1 - lastCommaIndex >= 1 && cleanedString.length - 1 - lastCommaIndex <= 3)) {\r\n            numberToParse = cleanedString.replace(',', '.');\r\n        } else {\r\n            numberToParse = cleanedString.replace(/,/g, '');\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    else if (hasDot) {\r\n        const lastDotIndex = cleanedString.lastIndexOf('.');\r\n        if (lastDotIndex !== -1 && (cleanedString.length - 1 - lastDotIndex >= 1 && cleanedString.length - 1 - lastDotIndex <= 3)) {\r\n            numberToParse = cleanedString;\r\n        } else {\r\n            numberToParse = cleanedString.replace(/\\./g, '');\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    else {\r\n        numberToParse = cleanedString;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\n    if (numberToParse.endsWith('.') || numberToParse.endsWith(',')) {\r\n        numberToParse = numberToParse.slice(0, -1);\r\n    }\r\n    const parsedNumber = parseFloat(numberToParse);\r\n\r\n    if (isNaN(parsedNumber)) {\r\n        return \"0.00\";\r\n    }\r\n    return parsedNumber.toFixed(2);\r\n}\r\nfunction showTarifForUser(inputNumber) {\r\n   \r\n    const num = Number(inputNumber);\r\n\r\n    if (isNaN(num)) {\r\n        return \"0,00\";\r\n    }\r\n\r\n \r\n    const fixedNumString = num.toFixed(2);\r\n\r\n    const parts = fixedNumString.split('.');\r\n    let integerPart = parts[0];\r\n    const decimalPart = parts[1];\r\n\r\n    integerPart = integerPart.replace(/\\B(?=(\\d{3})+(?!\\d))/g, '.');\r\n\r\n    return `${integerPart},${decimalPart}`;\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Doesn't match up\r\n//                 perfectly with SimpleDateFormat formats, but\r\n//                 backwards-compatability was required.\r\n\r\n// ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n// These functions use the same 'format' strings as the\r\n// java.text.SimpleDateFormat class, with minor exceptions.\r\n// The format string consists of the following abbreviations:\r\n//\r\n// Field        | Full Form          | Short Form\r\n// -------------+--------------------+-----------------------\r\n// Year         | yyyy (4 digits)    | yy (2 digits), y (2 or 4 digits)\r\n// Month        | MMM (name or abbr.)| MM (2 digits), M (1 or 2 digits)\r\n//              | NNN (abbr.)        |\r\n// Day of Month | dd (2 digits)      | d (1 or 2 digits)\r\n// Day of Week  | EE (name)          | E (abbr)\r\n// Hour (1-12)  | hh (2 digits)      | h (1 or 2 digits)\r\n// Hour (0-23)  | HH (2 digits)      | H (1 or 2 digits)\r\n// Hour (0-11)  | KK (2 digits)      | K (1 or 2 digits)\r\n// Hour (1-24)  | kk (2 digits)      | k (1 or 2 digits)\r\n// Minute       | mm (2 digits)      | m (1 or 2 digits)\r\n// Second       | ss (2 digits)      | s (1 or 2 digits)\r\n// AM/PM        | a                  |\r\n//\r\n// NOTE THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN MM and mm! Month=MM, not mm!\r\n// Examples:\r\n//  \"MMM d, y\" matches: January 01, 2000\r\n//                      Dec 1, 1900\r\n//                      Nov 20, 00\r\n//  \"M/d/yy\"   matches: 01/20/00\r\n//                      9/2/00\r\n//  \"MMM dd, yyyy hh:mm:ssa\" matches: \"January 01, 2000 12:30:45AM\"\r\n// ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nvar MONTH_NAMES=new Array('January','February','March','April','May','June','July','August','September','October','November','December','Jan','Feb','Mar','Apr','May','Jun','Jul','Aug','Sep','Oct','Nov','Dec');\r\nvar DAY_NAMES=new Array('Sunday','Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday','Saturday','Sun','Mon','Tue','Wed','Thu','Fri','Sat');\r\nfunction LZ(x) {return(x<0||x>9?\"\":\"0\")+x}\r\n\r\n// ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n// isDate ( date_string, format_string )\r\n// Returns true if date string matches format of format string and\r\n// is a valid date. Else returns false.\r\n// It is recommended that you trim whitespace around the value before\r\n// passing it to this function, as whitespace is NOT ignored!\r\n// ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nfunction isDate(val,format) {\r\n\tvar date=getDateFromFormat(val,format);\r\n\tif (date==0) { return false; }\r\n\treturn true;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n// compareDates(date1,date1format,date2,date2format)\r\n//   Compare two date strings to see which is -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nfunction compareDates(date1,dateformat1,date2,dateformat2) {\r\n\tvar d1=getDateFromFormat(date1,dateformat1);\r\n\tvar ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n// formatDate (date_object, format)\r\n// Returns a date in the output format specified.\r\n// The format string uses the same H=date.getHours();\r\n\tvar m=date.getMinutes();\r\n\tvar s=date.getSeconds();\r\n\tvar yyyy,yy,MMM,MM,dd,hh,h,mm,ss,ampm,HH,H,KK,K,kk,k;\r\n\t// Convert real date parts into formatted versions\r\n\tvar value=new Object();\r\n\tif (y.length < 4) {y=\"\"+(y-0+1900);}\r\n\tvalue[\"y\"]=\"\"+y;\r\n\tvalue[\"yyyy\"]=y;\r\n\tvalue[\"yy\"]=y.substring(2,4);\r\n\tvalue[\"M\"]=M;\r\n\tvalue[\"MM\"]=LZ(M);\r\n\tvalue[\"MMM\"]=MONTH_NAMES[M-1];\r\n\tvalue[\"NNN\"]=MONTH_NAMES[M+11];\r\n\tvalue[\"d\"]=d;\r\n\tvalue[\"dd\"]=LZ(d);\r\n\tvalue[\"E\"]=DAY_NAMES[E+7];\r\n\tvalue[\"EE\"]=DAY_NAMES[E];\r\n\tvalue[\"H\"]=H;\r\n\tvalue[\"HH\"]=LZ(H);\r\n\tif ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n// Utility functions for parsing in getDateFromFormat()\r\n// ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nfunction _isInteger(val) {\r\n\tvar digits=\"1234567890\";\r\n\tfor (var i=0; i < val.length; i++) {\r\n\t\tif (digits.indexOf(val.charAt(i))==-1) { return false; }\r\n\t\t}\r\n\treturn true;\r\n\t}\r\nfunction _getInt(str,i,minlength,maxlength) {\r\n\tfor (var x=maxlength; x>=minlength; x--) {\r\n\t\tvar ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n// getDateFromFormat( date_string , format_string )\r\n//\r\n// This function takes a date string and a format string. If it does not match, it returns 0.\r\n// ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nfunction getDateFromFormat(val,format) trailing characters left in the value, it doesn't match\r\n\tif (i_val != val.length) { return 0; }\r\n\t// Is date valid for month?\r\n\tif (month==2) {\r\n\t\t// Check for leap year\r\n\t\tif ( ( (year%4==0)&&(year%100 != 0) ) || (year%400==0) ) { // leap year\r\n\t\t\tif (date > 29){ return 0; }\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse { if (date > 28) { return 0; } }\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tif number of possible date formats to get the value. It will try to\r\n// match against the following international formats, in this order:\r\n// y-M-d   MMM d, y   MMM d,y   y-MMM-d   d-MMM-y  MMM d\r\n// M/d/y   M-d-y      M.d.y     MMM-d     M/d      M-d\r\n// d/M/y   d-M-y      d.M.y     d-MMM     d/M      d-M\r\n// A second argument may be passed to instruct the method to search\r\n// for formats like d/M/y (european format) before M/d/y (American).\r\n// Returns a Date object or null if no patterns match.\r\n// ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nfunction parseDate(val) {\r\n\tvar preferEuro=(arguments.length==2)?arguments[1]:false;\r\n\tgeneralFormats=new Array('y-M-d','MMM d, y','MMM d,y','y-MMM-d','d-MMM-y','MMM d');\r\n\tmonthFirst=new Array('M/d/y','M-d-y','M.d.y','MMM-d','M/d','M-d');\r\n\tdateFirst =new Array('d/M/y','d-M-y','d.M.y','d-MMM','d/M','d-M');\r\n\tvar checkList=new Array('generalFormats',preferEuro?'dateFirst':'monthFirst',preferEuro?'monthFirst':'dateFirst');\r\n\tvar d=null;\r\n\tfor (var i=0; i<checkList.length; i++) {\r\n\t\tvar l=window[checkList[i]];\r\n\t\tfor (var j=0; j<l.length; j++) {\r\n\t\t\td=getDateFromFormat(val,l[j]);\r\n\t\t\tif (d!=0) { return new Date(d); }\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\treturn null;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n/* SOURCE FILE: PopupWindow.js */\r\n\r\n/*\r\nPopupWindow.js\r\nAuthor: Matt Kruse\r\nLast modified: 02/16/04\r\n\r\nDESCRIPTION: This object allows you to easily and quickly popup a window\r\nin a certain place. The window can either be a DIV or a separate browser\r\nwindow.\r\n\r\nCOMPATABILITY: Works with Netscape 4.x, 6.x, IE 5.x on Windows. Some small\r\npositioning errors - usually with Window positioning - occur on the\r\nMacintosh platform. Due to bugs in Netscape 4.x, populating the popup\r\nwindow with <STYLE> tags may cause errors.\r\n\r\nUSAGE:\r\n// Create an object for a WINDOW popup\r\nvar win = new PopupWindow();\r\n\r\n// Create an object for a DIV window using the DIV named 'mydiv'\r\nvar win = new PopupWindow('mydiv');\r\n\r\n// Set the window to automatically hide itself when the user clicks\r\n// anywhere else on the page except the popup\r\nwin.autoHide();\r\n\r\n// Show the window relative to the anchor name passed in\r\nwin.showPopup(anchorname);\r\n\r\n// Hide the popup\r\nwin.hidePopup();\r\n\r\n// Set the size of the popup window (only applies to WINDOW popups\r\nwin.setSize(width,height);\r\n\r\n// Populate the contents of the popup window that will be shown. If you\r\n// change the contents while it is displayed, you will need to refresh()\r\nwin.populate(string);\r\n\r\n// set the URL of the window, rather than populating its contents\r\n// manually\r\nwin.setUrl(\"http://www.site.com/\");\r\n\r\n// Refresh the contents of the popup\r\nwin.refresh();\r\n\r\n// Specify how many pixels to the right of the anchor the popup will appear\r\nwin.offsetX = 50;\r\n\r\n// Specify how many pixels below the anchor the popup will appear\r\nwin.offsetY = 100;\r\n\r\nNOTES:\r\n1) Requires the functions in AnchorPosition.js\r\n\r\n2) Your anchor tag MUST contain both NAME and ID attributes which are the\r\n   same. For example:\r\n   <A NAME=\"test\" ID=\"test\"> </A>\r\n\r\n3) There must be at least a space between <A> </A> for IE5.5 to see the\r\n   anchor tag correctly. Do not do <A></A> with no space.\r\n\r\n4) When a PopupWindow object is created, a handler for 'onmouseup' is\r\n   attached to any event handler you may have already defined. Do NOT define\r\n   an event handler for 'onmouseup' after you define a PopupWindow object or\r\n   the autoHide() will not work correctly.\r\n*/\r\n\r\n// Set the position of the popup window based on the anchor\r\nfunction PopupWindow_getXYPosition(anchorname) {\r\n\tvar coordinates;\r\n\tif (this.type == \"WINDOW\") {\r\n\t\tcoordinates = getAnchorWindowPosition(anchorname);\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse {\r\n\t\tcoordinates = getAnchorPosition(anchorname);\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tthis.x = coordinates.x;\r\n\tthis.y = coordinates.y;\r\n\t}\r\n// Set width/height of DIV/popup window\r\nfunction PopupWindow_setSize(width,height) {\r\n\tthis.width = width;\r\n\tthis.height = height;\r\n\t}\r\n// Fill the window with contents\r\nfunction PopupWindow_populate(contents) {\r\n\tthis.contents = contents;\r\n\tthis.populated = false;\r\n\t}\r\n// Set the URL to go to\r\nfunction PopupWindow_setUrl(url) {\r\n\tthis.url = url;\r\n\t}\r\n// Set the window popup properties\r\nfunction PopupWindow_setWindowProperties(props) {\r\n\tthis.windowProperties = props;\r\n\t}\r\n// Refresh the displayed contents of the popup\r\nfunction PopupWindow_refresh() {\r\n\tif (this.divName != null) {\r\n\t\t// refresh the DIV object\r\n\t\tif (this.use_gebi) {\r\n\t\t\tdocument.getElementById(this.divName).innerHTML = this.contents;\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse if (this.use_css) {\r\n\t\t\tdocument.all[this.divName].innerHTML = this.contents;\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse if (this.use_layers) {\r\n\t\t\tvar d = document.layers[this.divName];\r\n\t\t\td.document.open();\r\n\t\t\td.document.writeln(this.contents);\r\n\t\t\td.document.close();\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse {\r\n\t\tif (this.popupWindow != null && !this.popupWindow.closed) {\r\n\t\t\tif (this.url!=\"\") {\r\n\t\t\t\tthis.popupWindow.location.href=this.url;\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\telse {\r\n\t\t\t\tthis.popupWindow.document.open();\r\n\t\t\t\tthis.popupWindow.document.writeln(this.contents);\r\n\t\t\t\tthis.popupWindow.document.close();\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tthis.popupWindow.focus();\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n// Position and show the popup, relative to an anchor object\r\nfunction PopupWindow_showPopup(anchorname) {\r\n\tthis.getXYPosition(anchorname);\r\n\tthis.x += this.offsetX;\r\n\tthis.y += this.offsetY;\r\n\tif (!this.populated && (this.contents != \"\")) {\r\n\t\tthis.populated = true;\r\n\t\tthis.refresh();\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tif (this.divName != null) {\r\n\t\t// Show the DIV object\r\n\t\tif (this.use_gebi) {\r\n\t\t\tdocument.getElementById(this.divName).style.left = this.x + \"px\";\r\n\t\t\tdocument.getElementById(this.divName).style.top = this.y + \"px\";\r\n\t\t\tdocument.getElementById(this.divName).style.visibility = \"visible\";\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse if (this.use_css) {\r\n\t\t\tdocument.all[this.divName].style.left = this.x;\r\n\t\t\tdocument.all[this.divName].style.top = this.y;\r\n\t\t\tdocument.all[this.divName].style.visibility = \"visible\";\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse if (this.use_layers) {\r\n\t\t\tdocument.layers[this.divName].left = this.x;\r\n\t\t\tdocument.layers[this.divName].top = this.y;\r\n\t\t\tdocument.layers[this.divName].visibility = \"visible\";\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse {\r\n\t\tif (this.popupWindow == null || this.popupWindow.closed) {\r\n\t\t\t// If the popup window will go off-screen, move it so it doesn't\r\n\t\t\tif (this.x<0) { this.x=0; }\r\n\t\t\tif (this.y<0) { this.y=0; }\r\n\t\t\tif (screen && screen.availHeight) {\r\n\t\t\t\tif ((this.y + this.height) > screen.availHeight) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tthis.y = screen.availHeight - this.height;\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tif (screen && screen.availWidth) {\r\n\t\t\t\tif ((this.x + this.width) > screen.availWidth) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tthis.x = screen.availWidth - this.width;\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tvar avoidAboutBlank = window.opera || ( document.layers && !navigator.mimeTypes['*'] ) || navigator.vendor == 'KDE' || ( document.childNodes && !document.all && !navigator.taintEnabled );\r\n\t\t\tthis.popupWindow = window.open(avoidAboutBlank?\"\":\"about:blank\",\"window_\"+anchorname,this.windowProperties+\",width=\"+this.width+\",height=\"+this.height+\",screenX=\"+this.x+\",left=\"+this.x+\",screenY=\"+this.y+\",top=\"+this.y+\"\");\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tthis.refresh();\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n// Hide the popup\r\nfunction PopupWindow_hidePopup() {\r\n\tif (this.divName != null) {\r\n\t\tif (this.use_gebi) {\r\n\t\t\tdocument.getElementById(this.divName).style.visibility = \"hidden\";\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse if (this.use_css) {\r\n\t\t\tdocument.all[this.divName].style.visibility = \"hidden\";\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse if (this.use_layers) {\r\n\t\t\tdocument.layers[this.divName].visibility = \"hidden\";\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse {\r\n\t\tif (this.popupWindow && !this.popupWindow.closed) {\r\n\t\t\tthis.popupWindow.close();\r\n\t\t\tthis.popupWindow = null;\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n// Pass an event and return whether or not it was the popup DIV that was clicked\r\nfunction PopupWindow_isClicked(e) {\r\n\tif (this.divName != null) {\r\n\t\tif (this.use_layers) {\r\n\t\t\tvar clickX = e.pageX;\r\n\t\t\tvar clickY = e.pageY;\r\n\t\t\tvar t = document.layers[this.divName];\r\n\t\t\tif ((clickX > t.left) && (clickX < t.left+t.clip.width) && (clickY > t.top) && (clickY < t.top+t.clip.height)) {\r\n\t\t\t\treturn true;\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\telse { return false; }\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse if (document.all) { // Need to hard-code this to trap IE for error-handling\r\n\t\t\tvar t = window.event.srcElement;\r\n\t\t\twhile (t.parentElement != null) {\r\n\t\t\t\tif (t.id==this.divName) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\treturn true;\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\tt = t.parentElement;\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\treturn false;\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse if (this.use_gebi && e) {\r\n\t\t\tvar t = e.originalTarget;\r\n\t\t\ttry{\r\n\t\t\twhile (t.parentNode != null) {\r\n\t\t\t\tif (t.id==this.divName) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\treturn true;\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\tt = t.parentNode;\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t}catch(e){}\r\n\t\t\treturn false;\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\treturn false;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\treturn false;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Check an onMouseDown event to see if we should hide\r\nfunction PopupWindow_hideIfNotClicked(e) {\r\n\tif (this.autoHideEnabled && !this.isClicked(e)) {\r\n\t\tthis.hidePopup();\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n// Call this to make the DIV disable automatically when mouse is clicked outside it\r\nfunction PopupWindow_autoHide() {\r\n\tthis.autoHideEnabled = true;\r\n\t}\r\n// This global function checks all PopupWindow objects onmouseup to see if they should be hidden\r\nfunction PopupWindow_hidePopupWindows(e) {\r\n\tfor (var i=0; i<popupWindowObjects.length; i++) {\r\n\t\tif (popupWindowObjects[i] != null) {\r\n\t\t\tvar p = popupWindowObjects[i];\r\n\t\t\tp.hideIfNotClicked(e);\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n// Run this immediately to attach the event listener\r\nfunction PopupWindow_attachListener() {\r\n\tif (document.layers) {\r\n\t\tdocument.captureEvents(Event.MOUSEUP);\r\n\t\t}\r\n\twindow.popupWindowOldEventListener = document.onmouseup;\r\n\tif (window.popupWindowOldEventListener != null) {\r\n\t\tdocument.onmouseup = new Function(\"window.popupWindowOldEventListener(); PopupWindow_hidePopupWindows();\");\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse {\r\n\t\tdocument.onmouseup = PopupWindow_hidePopupWindows;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n// CONSTRUCTOR for the PopupWindow object\r\n// Pass it a DIV name to use a DHTML popup, otherwise will default to window popup\r\nfunction PopupWindow() {\r\n\tif (!window.popupWindowIndex) { window.popupWindowIndex = 0; }\r\n\tif (!window.popupWindowObjects) { window.popupWindowObjects = new Array(); }\r\n\tif (!window.listenerAttached) {\r\n\t\twindow.listenerAttached = true;\r\n\t\tPopupWindow_attachListener();\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tthis.index = popupWindowIndex++;\r\n\tpopupWindowObjects[this.index] = this;\r\n\tthis.divName = null;\r\n\tthis.popupWindow = null;\r\n\tthis.width=0;\r\n\tthis.height=0;\r\n\tthis.populated = false;\r\n\tthis.visible = false;\r\n\tthis.autoHideEnabled = false;\r\n\r\n\tthis.contents = \"\";\r\n\tthis.url=\"\";\r\n\tthis.windowProperties=\"toolbar=no,location=no,status=no,menubar=no,scrollbars=auto,resizable,alwaysRaised,dependent,titlebar=no\";\r\n\tif (arguments.length>0) {\r\n\t\tthis.type=\"DIV\";\r\n\t\tthis.divName = arguments[0];\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse {\r\n\t\tthis.type=\"WINDOW\";\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tthis.use_gebi = false;\r\n\tthis.use_css = false;\r\n\tthis.use_layers = false;\r\n\tif (document.getElementById) { this.use_gebi = true; }\r\n\telse if (document.all) { this.use_css = true; }\r\n\telse if (document.layers) { this.use_layers = true; }\r\n\telse { this.type = \"WINDOW\"; }\r\n\tthis.offsetX = 0;\r\n\tthis.offsetY = 0;\r\n\t// Method mappings\r\n\tthis.getXYPosition = PopupWindow_getXYPosition;\r\n\tthis.populate = PopupWindow_populate;\r\n\tthis.setUrl = PopupWindow_setUrl;\r\n\tthis.setWindowProperties = PopupWindow_setWindowProperties;\r\n\tthis.refresh = PopupWindow_refresh;\r\n\tthis.showPopup = PopupWindow_showPopup;\r\n\tthis.hidePopup = PopupWindow_hidePopup;\r\n\tthis.setSize = PopupWindow_setSize;\r\n\tthis.isClicked = PopupWindow_isClicked;\r\n\tthis.autoHide = PopupWindow_autoHide;\r\n\tthis.hideIfNotClicked = PopupWindow_hideIfNotClicked;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n/* SOURCE FILE: CalendarPopup.js */\r\n\r\n// HISTORY\r\n// ------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n// Feb 7, 2005: Fixed a CSS styles to use px unit\r\n// March 29, 2004: Added check in select() method for the form field\r\n//      being disabled. If it is, just return and don't do anything.\r\n// March 24, 2004: Fixed bug - when month name and abbreviations were\r\n//      changed, date format still used original values.\r\n// January 26, 2004: Added support for drop-down month and year\r\n//      navigation (Thanks to Chris Reid for the idea)\r\n// September 22, 2003: Fixed a minor problem in YEAR calendar with\r\n//      CSS prefix.\r\n// August 19, 2003: Renamed the function to get styles, and made it\r\n//      work correctly without an object reference\r\n// August 18, 2003: Changed showYearNavigation and\r\n//      showYearNavigationInput to optionally take an argument of\r\n//      true or false\r\n// July 31, 2003: Added text input option for year navigation.\r\n//      Added a per-calendar CSS prefix option to optionally use\r\n//      different styles for different calendars.\r\n// July 29, 2003: Fixed bug causing the Today link to be clickable\r\n//      even though today falls in a disabled date range.\r\n//      Changed formatting to use pure CSS, allowing greater control\r\n//      over look-and-feel options.\r\n// June 11, 2003: Fixed bug causing the Today link to be unselectable\r\n//      under certain cases when some days of week are disabled\r\n// March 14, 2003: Added ability to disable individual dates or date\r\n//      ranges, display as light gray and strike-through\r\n// March 14, 2003: Removed dependency on graypixel.gif and instead\r\n///     use table border coloring\r\n// March 12, 2003: Modified showCalendar() function to allow optional\r\n//      start-date parameter\r\n// March 11, 2003: Modified select() function to allow optional\r\n//      start-date parameter\r\n/*\r\nDESCRIPTION: This object implements a popup calendar to allow the user to\r\nselect a date, month, quarter, or year.\r\n\r\nCOMPATABILITY: Works with Netscape 4.x, 6.x, IE 5.x on Windows. Some small\r\npositioning errors - usually with Window positioning - occur on the\r\nMacintosh platform.\r\nThe calendar can be modified to work for any location in the world by\r\nchanging which weekday is displayed as the first column, changing the month\r\nnames, and changing the column headers for each day.\r\n\r\nUSAGE:\r\n// Create a new CalendarPopup object of type WINDOW\r\nvar cal = new CalendarPopup();\r\n\r\n// Create a new CalendarPopup object of type DIV using the DIV named 'mydiv'\r\nvar cal = new CalendarPopup('mydiv');\r\n\r\n// Easy method to link the popup calendar with an input box.\r\ncal.select(inputObject, anchorname, dateFormat);\r\n// Same method, but passing a default date other than the field's current value\r\ncal.select(inputObject, anchorname, dateFormat, '01/02/2000');\r\n// This is an example call to the popup calendar from a link to populate an\r\n// input box. Note that to use this, date.js must also be included!!\r\n<A HREF=\"#\" onClick=\"cal.select(document.forms[0].date,'anchorname','MM/dd/yyyy'); return false;\">Select</A>\r\n\r\n// Set the type of date select to be used. By default it is 'date'.\r\ncal.setDisplayType(type);\r\n\r\n// When a date, month, quarter, or year is clicked, a function is called and\r\n// passed the details. You must write this function, and tell the calendar\r\n// popup what the function name is.\r\n// Function to be called for 'date' select receives y, m, d\r\ncal.setReturnFunction(functionname);\r\n// Function to be called for 'month' select receives y, m\r\ncal.setReturnMonthFunction(functionname);\r\n// Function to be called for 'quarter' select receives y, q\r\ncal.setReturnQuarterFunction(functionname);\r\n// Function to be called for 'year' select receives y\r\ncal.setReturnYearFunction(functionname);\r\n\r\n// Show the calendar relative to a given anchor\r\ncal.showCalendar(anchorname);\r\n\r\n// Hide the calendar. The calendar is set to autoHide automatically\r\ncal.hideCalendar();\r\n\r\n// Set the month names to be used. Default are English month names\r\ncal.setMonthNames(\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",...);\r\n\r\n// Set the month abbreviations to be used. Default are English month abbreviations\r\ncal.setMonthAbbreviations(\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",...);\r\n\r\n// Show navigation for changing by the year, not just one month at a time\r\ncal.showYearNavigation();\r\n\r\n// Show month and year dropdowns, for quicker selection of month of dates\r\ncal.showNavigationDropdowns();\r\n\r\n// Set the text to be used above each day column. The days start with\r\n// sunday regardless of the value of WeekStartDay\r\ncal.setDayHeaders(\"S\",\"M\",\"T\",...);\r\n\r\n// Set the day for the first column in the calendar grid. By default this\r\n// is Sunday (0) but it may be changed to fit the conventions of other\r\n// countries.\r\ncal.setWeekStartDay(1); // week is Monday - Sunday\r\n\r\n// Set the weekdays which should be disabled in the 'date' select popup. You can\r\n// then allow someone to only select week end dates, or Tuedays, for example\r\ncal.setDisabledWeekDays(0,1); // To disable selecting the 1st or 2nd days of the week\r\n\r\n// Selectively disable individual days or date ranges. Disabled days will not\r\n// be clickable, and show as strike-through text on current browsers.\r\n// Date format is any format recognized by parseDate() in date.js\r\n// Pass a single date to disable:\r\ncal.addDisabledDates(\"2003-01-01\");\r\n// Pass null as the first parameter to mean \"anything up to and including\" the\r\n// passed date:\r\ncal.addDisabledDates(null, \"01/02/03\");\r\n// Pass null as the second parameter to mean \"including the passed date and\r\n// anything after it:\r\ncal.addDisabledDates(\"Jan 01, 2003\", null);\r\n// Pass two dates to disable all dates inbetween and including the two\r\ncal.addDisabledDates(\"January 01, 2003\", \"Dec 31, 2003\");\r\n\r\n// When the 'year' select is displayed, set the number of years back from the\r\n// current year to start listing years. Default is 2.\r\n// This is also used for year drop-down, to decide how many years +/- to display\r\ncal.setYearSelectStartOffset(2);\r\n\r\n// Text for the word \"Today\" appearing on the calendar\r\ncal.setTodayText(\"Today\");\r\n\r\n// The calendar uses CSS classes for formatting. If you want your calendar to\r\n// have unique styles, you can set the prefix that will be added to all the\r\n// classes in the output.\r\n// For example, normal output may have this:\r\n//     <SPAN CLASS=\"cpTodayTextDisabled\">Today<SPAN>\r\n// But if you set the prefix like this:\r\ncal.setCssPrefix(\"Test\");\r\n// The output will then look like:\r\n//     <SPAN CLASS=\"TestcpTodayTextDisabled\">Today<SPAN>\r\n// And you can define that style somewhere in your page.\r\n\r\n// When using Year navigation, you can make the year be an input box, so\r\n// the user can manually change it and jump to any year\r\ncal.showYearNavigationInput();\r\n\r\n// Set the calendar offset to be different than the default. By default it\r\n// will appear just below and to the right of the anchorname. So if you have\r\n// a text box where the date will go and and anchor immediately after the\r\n// text box, the calendar will display immediately under the text box.\r\ncal.offsetX = 20;\r\ncal.offsetY = 20;\r\n\r\nNOTES:\r\n1) Requires the functions in AnchorPosition.js and PopupWindow.js\r\n\r\n2) Your anchor tag MUST contain both NAME and ID attributes which are the\r\n   same. For example:\r\n   <A NAME=\"test\" ID=\"test\"> </A>\r\n\r\n3) There must be at least a space between <A> </A> for IE5.5 to see the\r\n   anchor tag correctly. Do not do <A></A> with no space.\r\n\r\n4) When a CalendarPopup object is created, a handler for 'onmouseup' is\r\n   attached to any event handler you may have already defined. Do NOT define\r\n   an event handler for 'onmouseup' after you define a CalendarPopup object\r\n   or the autoHide() will not work correctly.\r\n\r\n5) The calendar popup display uses style sheets to make it look nice.\r\n\r\n*/\r\n\r\n// CONSTRUCTOR for the CalendarPopup Object\r\nfunction CalendarPopup() {\r\n\tvar c;\r\n\tif (arguments.length>0) {\r\n\t\tc = new CP_setCssPrefix;\r\n\tc.showNavigationDropdowns = CP_showNavigationDropdowns;\r\n\tc.showYearNavigationInput = CP_showYearNavigationInput;\r\n\tc.copyMonthNamesToWindow();\r\n\t// Return the object\r\n\treturn c;\r\n\t}\r\nfunction CP_copyMonthNamesToWindow() {\r\n\t// Copy these values over to the date.js\r\n\tif (typeof(window.MONTH_NAMES)!=\"undefined\" && window.MONTH_NAMES!=null) {\r\n\t\twindow.MONTH_NAMES = new Array();\r\n\t\tfor (var i=0; i<this.monthNames.length; i++) {\r\n\t\t\twindow.MONTH_NAMES[window.MONTH_NAMES.length] = this.monthNames[i];\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\tfor (var i=0; i<this.monthAbbreviations.length; i++) {\r\n\t\t\twindow.MONTH_NAMES[window.MONTH_NAMES.length] = this.monthAbbreviations[i];\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n// Temporary default functions to be called when items clicked, so no error is thrown\r\nfunction CP_tmpReturnFunction(y,m,d) {\r\n\tif (window.CP_targetInput!=null) {\r\n\t\tvar dt = new Date(y,m-1,d,0,0,0);\r\n\t\tif (window.CP_calendarObject!=null) { window.CP_calendarObject.copyMonthNamesToWindow(); }\r\n\t\twindow.CP_targetInput.value = formatDate(dt,window.CP_dateFormat);\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse {\r\n\t\talert('Use setReturnFunction() to define which function will get the clicked results!');\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\nfunction CP_tmpReturnMonthFunction(y,m) {\r\n\talert('Use setReturnMonthFunction() to define which function will get the clicked results!\\nYou clicked: year='+y+' , month='+m);\r\n\t}\r\nfunction CP_tmpReturnQuarterFunction(y,q) {\r\n\talert('Use setReturnQuarterFunction() to define which function will get the clicked results!\\nYou clicked: year='+y+' , quarter='+q);\r\n\t}\r\nfunction CP_tmpReturnYearFunction(y) {\r\n\talert('Use setReturnYearFunction() to define which function will get the clicked results!\\nYou clicked: year='+y);\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Set the name of the functions to call to get the clicked item\r\nfunction CP_setReturnFunction(name) { this.returnFunction = name; }\r\nfunction CP_setReturnMonthFunction(name) { this.returnMonthFunction = name; }\r\nfunction CP_setReturnQuarterFunction(name) { this.returnQuarterFunction = name; }\r\nfunction CP_setReturnYearFunction(name) { this.returnYearFunction = name; }\r\n\r\n// Over-ride the built-in month names\r\nfunction CP_setMonthNames() {\r\n\tfor (var i=0; i<arguments.length; i++) { CP_setDayHeaders() {\r\n\tfor (var i=0; i<arguments.length; i++) { this.dayHeaders[i] = arguments[i]; }\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Set the day of the week (0-7) that the calendar display starts on\r\n// This is for countries other than the US whose calendar displays start on Monday(1), for example\r\nfunction CP_setWeekStartDay(day) { this.weekStartDay = day; }\r\n\r\n// Show next/last year navigation links\r\nfunction CP_showYearNavigation() { this.isShowYearNavigation = (arguments.length>0)?arguments[0]:true; }\r\n\r\n// Which type of calendar to display\r\nfunction CP_setDisplayType(type) {\r\n\tif (type!=\"date\"&&type!=\"week-end\"&&type!=\"month\"&&type!=\"quarter\"&&type!=\"year\") { alert(\"Invalid display type! Must be one of: date,week-end,month,quarter,year\"); return false; }\r\n\tthis.displayType=type;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// How many years back to start by default for year display\r\nfunction CP_setYearSelectStartOffset(num) { this.yearSelectStartOffset=num; }\r\n\r\n// Set which weekdays should not be clickable\r\nfunction CP_setDisabledWeekDays() {\r\n\tthis.disabledWeekDays = new Object();\r\n\tfor (var i=0; i<arguments.length; i++) { this.disabledWeekDays[arguments[i]] = true; }\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Disable individual dates or ranges\r\n// Builds an internal logical test which is run via eval() for efficiency\r\nfunction CP_addDisabledDates(start, end) {\r\n\tif (arguments.length==1) { end=start; }\r\n\tif (start==null && end==null) { return; }\r\n\tif (this.disabledDatesExpression!=\"\") { this.disabledDatesExpression+= \"||\"; }\r\n\tif (start!=null) { start = parseDate(start); start=\"\"+start.getFullYear()+LZ(start.getMonth()+1)+LZ(start.getDate());}\r\n\tif (end!=null) { end=parseDate(end); end=\"\"+end.getFullYear()+LZ(end.getMonth()+1)+LZ(end.getDate());}\r\n\tif (start==null) { this.disabledDatesExpression+=\"(ds<=\"+end+\")\"; }\r\n\telse if (end  ==null) { this.disabledDatesExpression+=\"(ds>=\"+start+\")\"; }\r\n\telse { this.disabledDatesExpression+=\"(ds>=\"+start+\"&&ds<=\"+end+\")\"; }\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Set the text to use for the \"Today\" link\r\nfunction CP_setTodayText(text) {\r\n\tthis.todayText = text;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Set the prefix to be added to all CSS classes when writing output\r\nfunction CP_setCssPrefix(val) {\r\n\tthis.cssPrefix = val;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Show the navigation as an dropdowns that can be manually changed\r\nfunction CP_showNavigationDropdowns() { this.isShowNavigationDropdowns = (arguments.length>0)?arguments[0]:true; }\r\n\r\n// Show the year navigation as an input box that can be manually changed\r\nfunction CP_showYearNavigationInput() { this.isShowYearNavigationInput = (arguments.length>0)?arguments[0]:true; }\r\n\r\n// Hide a calendar object\r\nfunction CP_hideCalendar() {\r\n\tif (arguments.length > 0) { window.popupWindowObjects[arguments[0]].hidePopup(); }\r\n\telse { this.hidePopup(); }\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Refresh the contents of the calendar display\r\nfunction CP_refreshCalendar(index) {\r\n\tvar calObject = window.popupWindowObjects[index];\r\n\tif (arguments.length>1) {\r\n\t\tcalObject.populate(calObject.getCalendar(arguments[1],arguments[2],arguments[3],arguments[4],arguments[5]));\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse {\r\n\t\tcalObject.populate(calObject.getCalendar());\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tcalObject.refresh();\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Populate the calendar and display it\r\nfunction CP_showCalendar(anchorname) {\r\n\tif (arguments.length>1) {\r\n\t\tif (arguments[1]==null||arguments[1]==\"\") {\r\n\t\t\tthis.currentDate=new Date();\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse {\r\n\t\t\tthis.currentDate=new Date(parseDate(arguments[1]));\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tthis.populate(this.getCalendar());\r\n\tthis.showPopup(anchorname);\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Simple method to interface popup calendar with a text-entry box\r\nfunction CP_select(inputobj, linkname, format) {\r\n\tvar selectedDate=(arguments.length>3)?arguments[3]:null;\r\n\tif (!window.getDateFromFormat) {\r\n\t\talert(\"calendar.select: To use this method you must also include 'date.js' for date formatting\");\r\n\t\treturn;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tif (this.displayType!=\"date\"&&this.displayType!=\"week-end\") {\r\n\t\talert(\"calendar.select: This function can only be used with displayType 'date' or 'week-end'\");\r\n\t\treturn;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tif (inputobj.type!=\"text\" && inputobj.type!=\"hidden\" && inputobj.type!=\"textarea\") {\r\n\t\talert(\"calendar.select: Input object passed is not a valid form input object\");\r\n\t\twindow.CP_targetInput=null;\r\n\t\treturn;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tif (inputobj.disabled) { return; } // Can't use calendar input on disabled form input!\r\n\twindow.CP_targetInput = inputobj;\r\n\twindow.CP_calendarObject = this;\r\n\tthis.currentDate=null;\r\n\tvar time=0;\r\n\tif (selectedDate!=null) {\r\n\t\ttime = getDateFromFormat(selectedDate,format)\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse if (inputobj.value!=\"\") {\r\n\t\ttime = getDateFromFormat(inputobj.value,format);\r\n\t\t}\r\n\tif (selectedDate!=null || inputobj.value!=\"\") {\r\n\t\tif (time==0) { this.currentDate=null; }\r\n\t\telse { this.currentDate=new Date(time); }\r\n\t\t}\r\n\twindow.CP_dateFormat = format;\r\n\tthis.showCalendar(linkname);\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Get style block needed to display the calendar correctly\r\nfunction getCalendarStyles() {\r\n\tvar result = \"\";\r\n\tvar p = \"\";\r\n\tif (this!=null && typeof(this.cssPrefix)!=\"undefined\" && this.cssPrefix!=null && this.cssPrefix!=\"\") { p=this.cssPrefix; }\r\n\tresult += \"<STYLE>\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \".\"+p+\"cpYearNavigation,.\"+p+\"cpMonthNavigation { background-color:#C0C0C0; text-align:center; vertical-align:center; text-decoration:none; color:#000000; font-weight:bold; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \".\"+p+\"cpDayColumnHeader, .\"+p+\"cpYearNavigation,.\"+p+\"cpMonthNavigation,.\"+p+\"cpCurrentMonthDate,.\"+p+\"cpCurrentMonthDateDisabled,.\"+p+\"cpOtherMonthDate,.\"+p+\"cpOtherMonthDateDisabled,.\"+p+\"cpCurrentDate,.\"+p+\"cpCurrentDateDisabled,.\"+p+\"cpTodayText,.\"+p+\"cpTodayTextDisabled,.\"+p+\"cpText { font-family:arial; font-size:8pt; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \"TD.\"+p+\"cpDayColumnHeader { text-align:right; border:solid thin #C0C0C0;border-width:0px 0px 1px 0px; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \".\"+p+\"cpCurrentMonthDate, .\"+p+\"cpOtherMonthDate, .\"+p+\"cpCurrentDate  { text-align:right; text-decoration:none; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \".\"+p+\"cpCurrentMonthDateDisabled, .\"+p+\"cpOtherMonthDateDisabled, .\"+p+\"cpCurrentDateDisabled { color:#D0D0D0; text-align:right; text-decoration:line-through; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \".\"+p+\"cpCurrentMonthDate, .cpCurrentDate { color:#000000; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \".\"+p+\"cpOtherMonthDate { color:#808080; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \"TD.\"+p+\"cpCurrentDate { color:white; background-color: #C0C0C0; border-width:1px; border:solid thin #800000; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \"TD.\"+p+\"cpCurrentDateDisabled { border-width:1px; border:solid thin #FFAAAA; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \"TD.\"+p+\"cpTodayText, TD.\"+p+\"cpTodayTextDisabled { border:solid thin #C0C0C0; border-width:1px 0px 0px 0px;}\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \"A.\"+p+\"cpTodayText, SPAN.\"+p+\"cpTodayTextDisabled { height:20px; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \"A.\"+p+\"cpTodayText { color:black; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \".\"+p+\"cpTodayTextDisabled { color:#D0D0D0; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \".\"+p+\"cpBorder { border:solid thin #808080; }\\n\";\r\n\tresult += \"</STYLE>\\n\";\r\n\treturn result;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n// Return a string containing all the calendar code to be displayed\r\nfunction CP_getCalendar() {\r\n\tvar now = new Date();\r\n\t// Reference to window\r\n\tif (this.type == \"WINDOW\") { var windowref = \"window.opener.\"; }\r\n\telse { var windowref = \"\"; }\r\n\tvar result = \"\";\r\n\t// If POPUP, write entire HTML document\r\n\tif (this.type == \"WINDOW\") {\r\n\t\tresult += \"<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Calendar</TITLE>\"+this.getStyles()+\"</HEAD><BODY MARGINWIDTH=0 MARGINHEIGHT=0 TOPMARGIN=0 RIGHTMARGIN=0 LEFTMARGIN=0>\\n\";\r\n\t\tresult += '<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 BORDERWIDTH=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>\\n';\r\n\t\t}\r\n\telse {\r\n\t\tresult += '<TABLE CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpBorder\" WIDTH=144 BORDER=1 BORDERWIDTH=1 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=1>\\n';\r\n\t\tresult += '<TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER>\\n';\r\n\t\tresult += '<CENTER>\\n';\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t// Code for DATE display (default)\r\n\t// -------------------------------\r\n\tif (this.displayType==\"date\" || this.displayType==\"week-end\") {\r\n\t\tif (this.currentDate==null) { this.currentDate = now; }\r\n\t\tif (arguments.length > 0) { var month = arguments[0]; }\r\n\t\t\telse { var month = this.currentDate.getMonth()+1; }\r\n\t\tif (arguments.length > 1 && arguments[1]>0 && arguments[1]-0==arguments[1]) { var year = arguments[1]; }\r\n\t\t\telse { var year = this.currentDate.getFullYear(); }\r\n\t\tvar daysinmonth= new Array(0,31,28,31,30,31,30,31,31,30,31,30,31);\r\n\t\tif ( ( (year%4 == 0)&&(year%100 != 0) ) || (year%400 == 0) ) {\r\n\t\t\tdaysinmonth[2] = 29;\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tvar current_month = new Date(year,month-1,1);\r\n\t\tvar display_year = year;\r\n\t\tvar display_month = month;\r\n\t\tvar display_date = 1;\r\n\t\tvar weekday= current_month.getDay();\r\n\t\tvar offset = 0;\r\n\r\n\t\toffset = (weekday >= this.weekStartDay) ? weekday-this.weekStartDay : 7-this.weekStartDay+weekday ;\r\n\t\tif (offset > 0) {\r\n\t\t\tdisplay_month--;\r\n\t\t\tif (display_month < 1) { display_month = 12; display_year--; }\r\n\t\t\tdisplay_date = daysinmonth[display_month]-offset+1;\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tvar next_month = month+1;\r\n\t\tvar next_month_year = year;\r\n\t\tif (next_month > 12) { next_month=1; next_month_year++; }\r\n\t\tvar last_month = month-1;\r\n\t\tvar last_month_year = year;\r\n\t\tif (last_month < 1) { last_month=12; last_month_year--; }\r\n\t\tvar date_class;\r\n\t\tif (this.type!=\"WINDOW\") {\r\n\t\t\tresult += \"<TABLE WIDTH=144 BORDER=0 BORDERWIDTH=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>\";\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tresult += '<TR>\\n';\r\n\t\tvar refresh = windowref+'CP_refreshCalendar';\r\n\t\tvar refreshLink = 'javascript:' + refresh;\r\n\t\tif (this.isShowNavigationDropdowns) {\r\n\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" WIDTH=\"78\" COLSPAN=\"3\"><select CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" name=\"cpMonth\" onChange=\"'+refresh+'('+this.index+',this.options[this.selectedIndex].value-0,'+(year-0)+');\">';\r\n\t\t\tfor( var monthCounter=1; monthCounter<=12; monthCounter++ ) {\r\n\t\t\t\tvar selected = (monthCounter==month) ? 'SELECTED' : '';\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<option value=\"'+monthCounter+'\" '+selected+'>'+this.monthNames[monthCounter-1]+'</option>';\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tresult += '</select></TD>';\r\n\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" WIDTH=\"10\">&nbsp;</TD>';\r\n\r\n\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" WIDTH=\"56\" COLSPAN=\"3\"><select CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" name=\"cpYear\" onChange=\"'+refresh+'('+this.index+','+month+',this.options[this.selectedIndex].value-0);\">';\r\n\t\t\tfor( var yearCounter=year-this.yearSelectStartOffset; yearCounter<=year+this.yearSelectStartOffset; yearCounter++ ) {\r\n\t\t\t\tvar selected = (yearCounter==year) ? 'SELECTED' : '';\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<option value=\"'+yearCounter+'\" '+selected+'>'+yearCounter+'</option>';\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tresult += '</select></TD>';\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse {\r\n\t\t\tif (this.isShowYearNavigation) {\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" WIDTH=\"10\"><A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" HREF=\"'+refreshLink+'('+this.index+','+last_month+','+last_month_year+');\">&lt;</A></TD>';\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" WIDTH=\"58\"><SPAN CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\">'+this.monthNames[month-1]+'</SPAN></TD>';\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" WIDTH=\"10\"><A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" HREF=\"'+refreshLink+'('+this.index+','+next_month+','+next_month_year+');\">&gt;</A></TD>';\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" WIDTH=\"10\">&nbsp;</TD>';\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" WIDTH=\"10\"><A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" HREF=\"'+refreshLink+'('+this.index+','+month+','+(year-1)+');\">&lt;</A></TD>';\r\n\t\t\t\tif (this.isShowYearNavigationInput) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" WIDTH=\"36\"><INPUT NAME=\"cpYear\" CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" SIZE=\"4\" MAXLENGTH=\"4\" VALUE=\"'+year+'\" onBlur=\"'+refresh+'('+this.index+','+month+',this.value-0);\"></TD>';\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\telse {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" WIDTH=\"36\"><SPAN CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\">'+year+'</SPAN></TD>';\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" WIDTH=\"10\"><A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" HREF=\"'+refreshLink+'('+this.index+','+month+','+(year+1)+');\">&gt;</A></TD>';\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\telse {\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" WIDTH=\"22\"><A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" HREF=\"'+refreshLink+'('+this.index+','+last_month+','+last_month_year+');\">&lt;&lt;</A></TD>\\n';\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" WIDTH=\"100\"><SPAN CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\">'+this.monthNames[month-1]+' '+year+'</SPAN></TD>\\n';\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" WIDTH=\"22\"><A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpMonthNavigation\" HREF=\"'+refreshLink+'('+this.index+','+next_month+','+next_month_year+');\">&gt;&gt;</A></TD>\\n';\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tresult += '</TR></TABLE>\\n';\r\n\t\tresult += '<TABLE WIDTH=120 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=1 ALIGN=CENTER>\\n';\r\n\t\tresult += '<TR>\\n';\r\n\t\tfor (var j=0; j<7; j++) {\r\n\r\n\t\t\tresult += '<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpDayColumnHeader\" WIDTH=\"14%\"><SPAN CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpDayColumnHeader\">'+this.dayHeaders[(this.weekStartDay+j)%7]+'</TD>\\n';\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tresult += '</TR>\\n';\r\n\t\tfor (var row=1; row<=6; row++) {\r\n\t\t\tresult += '<TR>\\n';\r\n\t\t\tfor (var col=1; col<=7; col++) {\r\n\t\t\t\tvar disabled=false;\r\n\t\t\t\tif (this.disabledDatesExpression!=\"\") {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tvar ds=\"\"+display_year+LZ(display_month)+LZ(display_date);\r\n\t\t\t\t\teval(\"disabled=(\"+this.disabledDatesExpression+\")\");\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\tvar dateClass = \"\";\r\n\t\t\t\tif ((display_month == this.currentDate.getMonth()+1) && (display_date==this.currentDate.getDate()) && (display_year==this.currentDate.getFullYear())) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tdateClass = \"cpCurrentDate\";\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\telse if (display_month == month) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tdateClass = \"cpCurrentMonthDate\";\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\telse {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tdateClass = \"cpOtherMonthDate\";\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\tif (disabled || this.disabledWeekDays[col-1]) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tresult += '\t<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+dateClass+'\"><SPAN CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+dateClass+'Disabled\">'+display_date+'</SPAN></TD>\\n';\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\telse {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tvar selected_date = display_date;\r\n\t\t\t\t\tvar selected_month = display_month;\r\n\t\t\t\t\tvar selected_year = display_year;\r\n\t\t\t\t\tif (this.displayType==\"week-end\") {\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tvar d = new Date(selected_year,selected_month-1,selected_date,0,0,0,0);\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\td.setDate(d.getDate() + (7-col));\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tselected_year = d.getYear();\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tif (selected_year < 1000) { selected_year += 1900; }\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tselected_month = d.getMonth()+1;\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tselected_date = d.getDate();\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\t\tresult += '\t<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+dateClass+'\"><A HREF=\"javascript:'+windowref+this.returnFunction+'('+selected_year+','+selected_month+','+selected_date+');'+windowref+'CP_hideCalendar(\\''+this.index+'\\');\" CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+dateClass+'\">'+display_date+'</A></TD>\\n';\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\tdisplay_date++;\r\n\t\t\t\tif (display_date > daysinmonth[display_month]) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tdisplay_date=1;\r\n\t\t\t\t\tdisplay_month++;\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\tif (display_month > 12) {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tdisplay_month=1;\r\n\t\t\t\t\tdisplay_year++;\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tresult += '</TR>';\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tvar current_weekday = now.getDay() - this.weekStartDay;\r\n\t\tif (current_weekday < 0) {\r\n\t\t\tcurrent_weekday += 7;\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tresult += '<TR>\\n';\r\n\t\tresult += '\t<TD COLSPAN=7 ALIGN=CENTER CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpTodayText\">\\n';\r\n\t\tif (this.disabledDatesExpression!=\"\") {\r\n\t\t\tvar ds=\"\"+now.getFullYear()+LZ(now.getMonth()+1)+LZ(now.getDate());\r\n\t\t\teval(\"disabled=(\"+this.disabledDatesExpression+\")\");\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tif (disabled || this.disabledWeekDays[current_weekday+1]) {\r\n\t\t\tresult += '\t\t<SPAN CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpTodayTextDisabled\">'+this.todayText+'</SPAN>\\n';\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\telse {\r\n\t\t\tresult += '\t\t<A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpTodayText\" HREF=\"javascript:'+windowref+this.returnFunction+'(\\''+now.getFullYear()+'\\',\\''+(now.getMonth()+1)+'\\',\\''+now.getDate()+'\\');'+windowref+'CP_hideCalendar(\\''+this.index+'\\');\">'+this.todayText+'</A>\\n';\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tresult += '\t\t<BR>\\n';\r\n\t\tresult += '\t</TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></TD></TR></TABLE>\\n';\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\t// Code common for MONTH, QUARTER, YEAR\r\n\t// ------------------------------------\r\n\tif (this.displayType==\"month\" || this.displayType==\"quarter\" || this.displayType==\"year\") {\r\n\t\tif (arguments.length > 0) { var year = arguments[0]; }\r\n\t\telse {\r\n\t\t\tif (this.displayType==\"year\") {\tvar year = now.getFullYear()-this.yearSelectStartOffset; }\r\n\t\t\telse { var year = now.getFullYear(); }\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tif (this.displayType!=\"year\" && this.isShowYearNavigation) {\r\n\t\t\tresult += \"<TABLE WIDTH=144 BORDER=0 BORDERWIDTH=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>\";\r\n\t\t\tresult += '<TR>\\n';\r\n\t\t\tresult += '\t<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" WIDTH=\"22\"><A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" HREF=\"javascript:'+windowref+'CP_refreshCalendar('+this.index+','+(year-1)+');\">&lt;&lt;</A></TD>\\n';\r\n\t\t\tresult += '\t<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" WIDTH=\"100\">'+year+'</TD>\\n';\r\n\t\t\tresult += '\t<TD CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" WIDTH=\"22\"><A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpYearNavigation\" HREF=\"javascript:'+windowref+'CP_refreshCalendar('+this.index+','+(year+1)+');\">&gt;&gt;</A></TD>\\n';\r\n\t\t\tresult += '</TR></TABLE>\\n';\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t// Code for MONTH display\r\n\t// ----------------------\r\n\tif (this.displayType==\"month\") {\r\n\t\t// If POPUP, write entire HTML document\r\n\t\tresult += '<TABLE WIDTH=120 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER>\\n';\r\n\t\tfor (var i=0; i<4; i++) {\r\n\t\t\tresult += '<TR>';\r\n\t\t\tfor (var j=0; j<3; j++) {\r\n\t\t\t\tvar monthindex = ((i*3)+j);\r\n\t\t\t\tresult += '<TD WIDTH=33% ALIGN=CENTER><A CLASS=\"'+this.cssPrefix+'cpText\" HREF=\"javascript:'+windowref+this.returnMonthFunction+'('+year+','+(monthindex+1)+');'+windowref+'CP_hideCalendar(\\''+this.index+'\\');\" CLASS=\"'+date_class+'\">'+this.monthAbbreviations[monthindex]+'</A></TD>';\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tresult += '</TR>';\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\tresult += '</TABLE></CENTER></TD></TR></TABLE>\\n';\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t// Code for QUARTER display\r\n\t// ------------------------\r\n\tif (this.displayType==\"quarter\") {\r\n\t\tresult += '<BR><TABLE
